ZCZC GE86
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 292300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 965
CENTRED S OF ICELAND BRINGING A VERY STRG CYCLONIC FLOW
ACROSS FAIR ISLE WITH S WINDS BECMG STRG TO GALE FORCE.
WEAK HIGH PRESSURE LIES OVER THE EERN NORWEGIAN BASIN
THE N SEA AND ENGLISH CHANNEL. OVERNIGHT SUNDAY INTO
MONDAY THE DEEP LOW PRESSURE MOVS N AND BEGINS TO FILL
DISPLACING THE HIGH PRESSURE OVER THE NORWEGIAN BASIN
AND BRINGING STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE SW WINDS TO SEA
AREAS FAIR ISLE VIKING AND N UTSIRE. HIGH PRESSURE
PERSISTS OVER THE N SEA AND ENGLISH CHANNEL. OVERNIGHT
MONDAY INTO TUESDAY HIGH PRESSURE OVER SCANDINAVIA AND
THE N SEA BEGINS TO BUILD MAINTAINING A STRG SW FLOW
OVER FAIR ISLE BUT BRINGING LIGHT AND VRB WINDS
ELSEWHERE. OVERNIGHT TUESDAY INTO WEDNESDAY STRG SW WINDS
MIGRATE EWARDS AGAIN TO AFFECT FAIR ISLE VIKING AND N
UTSIRE.
